sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1732000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Donna Lee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: J23100 Promoter with a RBS (BBa_S04423), PelB Leader sequence, Gaussia princeps luciferase, and a B0015 terminator. Allows Gaussia princeps luciferase to be transcribed and translated using a strong promoter. Luminescence can be expressed by reacting the luciferase product with coelenterazine.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is codon optimized for E.coli. Sequence contains a PelB leader sequence that allows the Gaussia princeps luciferase proteins to secreted into the periplasmic space of the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Engineered from XXXXXXXX. Provided by the Bruchez lab at Carnegie Mellon.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K121016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shotaro Ayukawa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Restriction sites of Sal I, Bam HI, Bgl II, and Mlu I in front of strong RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We designed new prefix(Sal I and Bam HI) and suffix(Bgl II and Mul I) for insertions of promoters and regulator binding sites in front of RBS.
